334
00:27:22,868 --> 00:27:35,880
♪ <i>Love's testimony is not to be asked of it</i> ♪

335
00:27:35,950 --> 00:27:49,910
♪ <i>It pulls out tears and drops them from the eyes...</i> ♪

336
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,969
You want her to wear

337
00:27:53,069 --> 00:27:55,948
Red on her engagement?

338
00:27:55,948 --> 00:27:57,341
Keep it there.

339
00:27:57,341 --> 00:27:59,467
Show me something else.

340
00:28:01,910 --> 00:28:03,613
Aye...

341
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:06,568
She likes this one.

342
00:28:11,390 --> 00:28:13,758
Now you're talking.

343
00:28:14,888 --> 00:28:18,903
She'd look like a fairy in this one.

344
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:21,001
But I don't like it.

345
00:28:21,821 --> 00:28:24,882
I don't want her to look like a fairy.

346
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,979
I want her to look like a bride.

347
00:28:31,380 --> 00:28:33,008
A proper bride.

348
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:36,767
Covered, protected...

349
00:28:37,230 --> 00:28:39,059
But...

350
00:28:39,668 --> 00:28:42,879
What's wrong with this blue one?

351
00:28:43,710 --> 00:28:45,988
Remember, Ammi Begum,

352
00:28:47,658 --> 00:28:51,348
I wore a blue suit on my engagement.

353
00:28:54,010 --> 00:28:56,628
You said back then, too,

354
00:28:58,300 --> 00:29:02,238
'You look just like a fairy, Suraiyya'...

355
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:06,021
The higher your fairy flew,

356
00:29:06,700 --> 00:29:09,174
The harder she fell...

357
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:15,654
We'd rather not have another fairy here, Ammi Begum...

358
00:29:23,410 --> 00:29:26,019
Pick whatever you like.

359
00:29:26,109 --> 00:29:27,890
Just... Not this one.

360
00:31:00,690 --> 00:31:02,819
Tear that, will you?

361
00:31:02,938 --> 00:31:04,078
Why?

362
00:31:04,179 --> 00:31:06,650
It's time for a new picture.

363
00:31:06,650 --> 00:31:08,500
With you holding the gun.

364
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:12,150
Don't you think you're aiming for Waqar Ahmed's head?

365
00:31:12,150 --> 00:31:14,011
You're talking about aiming!

366
00:31:14,011 --> 00:31:16,222
I just pulled the trigger!

367
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:18,391
He's gonna die for real.

368
00:31:19,090 --> 00:31:20,178
No, he's not.

369
00:31:20,178 --> 00:31:21,388
Just on the rack.

370
00:31:21,388 --> 00:31:24,518
There's a hundred prerequisites to dying, my dear.

371
00:31:24,518 --> 00:31:27,087
The first... Is torment!

372
00:31:27,191 --> 00:31:28,958
That's what I was thinking.

373
00:31:28,958 --> 00:31:31,399
You won't let him die so easily.

374
00:31:31,399 --> 00:31:35,022
Well, guess what, he ain't going down that easy, Maheen Aurangzeb!

375
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,468
The living ought to know

376
00:31:37,468 --> 00:31:40,598
That those who die on purpose mean business!

377
00:31:46,710 --> 00:31:48,408
How much does he pay you?

378
00:31:48,408 --> 00:31:49,708
For?

379
00:31:49,768 --> 00:31:55,319
Running these campaigns for him, making a gentleman out of him, and shielding the nasty piece of work that he is?

380
00:31:55,352 --> 00:31:57,332
You know how nasty he is?

381
00:31:57,377 --> 00:32:00,448
Let's keep it under the wraps, shall we? Everyone loves him so much.

382
00:32:00,448 --> 00:32:02,260
Who doesn't know <i>him</i>?

383
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:04,371
<i>You</i> sure don't.

384
00:32:04,483 --> 00:32:05,948
It ain't that bad.

385
00:32:05,948 --> 00:32:07,709
I know him a bit too.

386
00:32:07,709 --> 00:32:10,790
When the London tramp gets tired of his English roses,

387
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:13,978
He comes to Pakistan for a change of taste!

388
00:32:14,388 --> 00:32:17,950
This time, he wanted to get the big fish.

389
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,203
Such as?

390
00:32:19,203 --> 00:32:21,864
Such as Maheen Aurangzeb!

391
00:32:23,184 --> 00:32:25,416
But his plot failed here.

392
00:32:25,416 --> 00:32:27,867
I made mincemeat of him!

393
00:32:29,870 --> 00:32:32,408
Care to tell me about <i>your</i> plot?

394
00:32:32,528 --> 00:32:34,309
I don't plot.

395
00:32:34,378 --> 00:32:37,008
I decide, my dear Fajr.

396
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:39,268
So...

397
00:32:39,268 --> 00:32:41,849
Getting engaged to Gulrez

398
00:32:41,919 --> 00:32:44,269
Is but your 'decision'?

399
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:48,739
Ever slept in peace

400
00:32:48,879 --> 00:32:51,409
Since you made this decision?

401
00:32:52,990 --> 00:32:55,248
Is your heart at ease for a moment?

402
00:32:55,398 --> 00:32:57,248
Doesn't it hurt?

403
00:32:59,430 --> 00:33:02,008
Doesn't it awaken you from your sleep

404
00:33:02,008 --> 00:33:06,088
And say, 'You're gonna ruin me in your revenge plot, you imbecile'!

405
00:33:09,310 --> 00:33:11,860
The least your poor heart would ask you

406
00:33:11,970 --> 00:33:14,330
Is if you actually got engaged on Sunday,

407
00:33:14,330 --> 00:33:16,321
What happens on Monday?

408
00:33:19,130 --> 00:33:22,878
There'll be no Sunday after this one, Maheen Aurangzeb.

409
00:33:24,638 --> 00:33:26,190
Days change,

410
00:33:26,248 --> 00:33:29,109
But changed days like to have their way.

411
00:33:29,610 --> 00:33:33,141
If you feel like torturing someone on Monday,

412
00:33:33,271 --> 00:33:36,682
You can't be sure that tramp's gonna be in the city to take it.

413
00:33:38,942 --> 00:33:41,222
What if he went back?

414
00:33:41,652 --> 00:33:43,191
What if

415
00:33:43,291 --> 00:33:45,622
He left on Sunday night?

416
00:33:59,230 --> 00:34:01,491
What if someone's told him...

417
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,570
'Don't come back again'

418
00:34:03,570 --> 00:34:05,461
'If you leave now'?

419
00:34:53,770 --> 00:34:55,979
What d'you say, Ammi Begum?

420
00:34:56,609 --> 00:34:57,689
Fajr...

421
00:34:57,748 --> 00:34:59,139
Call her here.

422
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:01,363
She ought to take her pick.

423
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:31,788
I figured I ought to tear it for real after you left.

424
00:35:31,888 --> 00:35:34,039
As I was about to, I thought...

425
00:35:34,119 --> 00:35:36,111
He wasn't always like that.

426
00:35:36,141 --> 00:35:38,973
All that's left of childhood is the memories...

427
00:35:38,973 --> 00:35:41,734
You ought to hold on to memories...

428
00:35:42,824 --> 00:35:44,564
But why are you here?

429
00:35:44,564 --> 00:35:46,710
Don't let his company spoil you!

430
00:35:46,710 --> 00:35:49,248
You shouldn't be peeping into others' rooms.

431
00:35:49,308 --> 00:35:50,668
D'you know,

432
00:35:50,668 --> 00:35:54,809
Eight people got engaged on Sundays in our family in the last 40 years.

433
00:35:54,838 --> 00:35:56,888
Just one broke.

434
00:35:57,048 --> 00:35:59,729
Because the girl didn't want to marry him.

435
00:35:59,950 --> 00:36:00,844
Please.

436
00:36:00,844 --> 00:36:02,825
No more of your balderdash.

437
00:36:03,635 --> 00:36:06,406
None of what I've said in the last few days

438
00:36:06,406 --> 00:36:08,827
Qualifies as balderdash.

439
00:36:12,350 --> 00:36:15,069
I've seen and heard it myself.

440
00:36:15,180 --> 00:36:17,039
He leaves on Sunday.

441
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:23,188
He was arguing with his agent.

442
00:36:24,778 --> 00:36:26,608
He wasn't so lucky

443
00:36:26,780 --> 00:36:29,011
As to get a flight

444
00:36:29,081 --> 00:36:31,513
Before Sunday.

445
00:36:33,270 --> 00:36:36,058
He'll be gone forever on Sunday.

446
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:37,918
Because I've asked him to.

447
00:36:37,978 --> 00:36:41,190
'Don't ever come back if you go'.

448
00:36:46,050 --> 00:36:48,170
He won't be coming back, Maheen.

449
00:36:48,990 --> 00:36:50,940
Ever.

